cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.CC, cs.GT, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with an algorithmic problem related to data structures (finding the maximum length), which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS category. Additionally, the problem involves geometric considerations (cutting sticks), which makes cs.CG a likely category as well. The paper also mentions the envy-free stick-division problem, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of dividing sticks equally among multiple parties can also be seen as a game-theoretic problem (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the structure of the problem and obtaining an optimal algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
